<br>
That'd be kinda neat.. <p>Level 50th Dorf Rogue of Cazic Thule, "for 20 levels all I smelt was goblin ass"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ruccus>Ruccus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 8:04:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://pages.sprint.ca/deanweb/files/PUCKSMALL.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Let me say from the outset it disturbs me to read Absor's post about rogues getting mobs to run across the zone via the evade skill.  Only on one occasion, on the very first day evade was implemented, has any mob left me and travelled any distance to attack someone else (who was only about 10 feet away).  I believe evade was quickly altered a day or two later to its' current state.<br>
<br>
I've been thinking over possible alternatives to any Evade changes, as the current proposal is no more than letting two rogues push a third out to be slaughtered, then the two remaining rogues trying to out-evade the other.  The suggestion to not get to the top spot in the first place would pretty much mean no more rogues as pullers.<br>
<br>
Part of the problem is the Taunt skill - It's not as effective as it should be.  This proposal combines evade with taunt to allow the group as a whole to be more accountable for its hate, and allow the tank in the group to absorb a majority of the damage.<br>
<br>
My proposal calls for every rogue to be given an <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;Evade pool&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  This pool will contain the amount of hate generated since the last successful evade.  The group as a whole would also have a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;Taunt pool&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, from which tanks can generate hate by taunting.<br>
<br>
With a successful evade, a percentage of the rogue's Evade pool will be deducted from his current hate and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  added</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the Taunt pool</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  the remaining hate in the Evade pool would be reset to zero.  A successful taunt by any of the group's tanks will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> give a percentage of the Taunt pool to the tank</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  This bonus hate would be added to whatever hate bonuses tanks normally get for taunting.<br>
<br>
In effect, by evading, the rogue will say &quot;I didn't do it - HE DID!&quot; (/em points to tank).<br>
<br>
By taunting, the tank would be saying &quot;Yeah, I did it - now what are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> going to do about it?!&quot;<br>
<br>
This allows evade to be effective in a group setting, yet still allow the group to be accountable for its' hate.<br>
<br>
With more than one rogue, the Taunt pool would fill quite quickly, maybe requiring the taunt pool to be capped at a certain level based on the average team level.<br>
<br>
The percentage method was probably dismissed because near the end of the fight, insane abouts of hate would be generated by the rogues - a flat percentage deduction that would be reasonable at the start of the fight would drop the rogue way down the hate list at the end of a fight.  <br>
<br>
With the &quot;Evade pool&quot; suggestion, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  less</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you evaded, the more potent it would become when you finally do decide to evade - kind of like the boy who cried wolf.  When the boy first cried wolf, everyone believed him, but when he kept doing it, it lost it's effectiveness.<br>
<br>
Plus, the rogue would also be relying on the tank to &quot;support&quot; the rogue's evading tactics by taunting - Evading as a solitary skill would technically still be nerfed, but the combination of evade and taunt together would actually be an improvement.<br>
